1
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:19,399
<i>Michael Jordan
has said it many times.</i>

2
00:00:19,436 --> 00:00:23,314
<i>He considers Madison Square Garden to be
the mecca of basketball.</i>

3
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:28,945
<i>If, in fact, this is his final
NBA All-Star Game,</i>

4
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:31,489
<i>it's a perfect place
to make a last statement.</i>

5
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:34,409
<i>On the verge
of a repeat three-peat,</i>

6
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:36,786
<i>Michael Jordan is playing his last year.</i>

7
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:40,331
<i>Bulls GM Jerry Krause swore on Wednesday</i>

8
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:43,001
<i>that Phil Jackson
would not return next year,</i>

9
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:45,462
<i>and said if Michael chooses to leave</i>

10
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:47,797
<i>because there was another coach,
then it's his choice.</i>

11
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,424
- Boy! Hey!
- What's up?

12
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:50,967
Hey, your feet look good!

13
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:55,680
<i>Kobe Bryant,
the youngest All-Star in history</i>

14
00:00:55,764 --> 00:00:58,725
<i>- at 19 years, five months.
- I've talked to him.</i>

15
00:00:58,808 --> 00:01:00,528
<i>It's the same thing.
He's a 19-year-old kid.</i>

16
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:04,105
<i>They're saying, "Kobe, you look ready
to be the man at the All-Star Game."</i>

17
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:06,357
<i>You can't forget the king
is still on the court.</i>

18
00:01:06,941 --> 00:01:09,027
<i>♪ If I ruled the world ♪</i>

19
00:01:10,361 --> 00:01:12,030
Michael's going here?

20
00:01:12,697 --> 00:01:14,967
- There you go.
<i>- </i>You get the chair.

21
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:18,369
Man, I must be the old guy.
I remember I used to be way in the back.

22
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:20,533
We gave you
a nice, comfortable chair.

23
00:01:26,961 --> 00:01:28,630
So you're feeling all right, huh?

24
00:01:29,047 --> 00:01:31,007
I guess so,
since you're gonna play me 40 minutes.

25
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:32,926
You better be ready.

26
00:01:33,009 --> 00:01:34,469
Good shots out there.

27
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:36,947
If you don't have anything
in the middle, kick it out,

28
00:01:36,971 --> 00:01:39,451
make that extra pass,
somebody should be wide open for a three.

29
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,268
While we're here, we might as well win.

30
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:43,832
- Yeah.
- Right?

31
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:47,148
That Laker boy's
gonna take everybody one-on-one.

32
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:48,399
I know, right?

33
00:01:48,483 --> 00:01:50,777
- Yeah!
- Who, Kobe? Yeah.

34
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:54,823
He don't let the game come
to him. He just go out there and take it.

35
00:01:56,324 --> 00:01:59,244
I'm going to make this shit happen.
I'm gonna make this a one-on-one game.

36
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:03,189
I figured after the first four
attempts didn't go in, he was gonna chill.

37
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:04,082
What?

38
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:05,792
After the first four attempts?

39
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:08,628
If I was his teammate,
I wouldn't pass him the fucking ball!

40
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:12,882
You want this ball again, brother,
you better rebound.

41
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:18,680
- This is the East locker room.
- Hold up, hold up.

42
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:21,200
- Got nothing to do with the West.
- Hold up.

43
00:02:21,224 --> 00:02:24,519
He got nothing
but his damn Laker colors on.

44
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:26,604
Yeah, yeah, like he coaching.

45
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:29,899
Now, I'm with the old motherf... Oops!

46
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:31,985
- The old mugs.
- There ain't many of us here.

47
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:34,320
That's why I come to say
"What's up?" to my boy.

48
00:02:34,404 --> 00:02:36,844
- What's happening? How you doing?
- How you feeling?

49
00:02:36,906 --> 00:02:37,906
Damn!

50
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:39,242
Good, man.

51
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:40,427
- Michael...
- I'm lovin' it.

52
00:02:40,451 --> 00:02:42,662
Would you like to have
some of his ass today?

53
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:45,582
Hey, you know
I'd be coming at him, Larry.

54
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:48,084
Just like I used to come
at both of y'all.

55
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:52,672
<i>Just about tip-off time
at Madison Square Garden</i>

56
00:02:52,755 --> 00:02:55,175
<i>for the 48th NBA All-Star Game.</i>

57
00:02:55,258 --> 00:02:57,886
<i>And there you see Kobe Bryant
in the foreground,</i>

58
00:02:57,969 --> 00:03:00,221
<i>the man many have dubbed
the next Michael Jordan.</i>

59
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:02,056
I got Mike, I got Mike.

60
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,975
- <i>Here is Michael.</i>
- Ah!

61
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:07,395
<i>Count it,
plus the foul for Jordan!</i>

62
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:13,276
I grew up watching Michael on TV,

63
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:15,737
and now you got a chance
to go face-to-face with him.

64
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:18,907
You get a chance to really see
and touch and feel...

65
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:23,369
the strength, speed, quickness. And, um...

66
00:03:23,995 --> 00:03:25,747
It was fun to be out there.

67
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:28,082
<i>He's got the ball
in his hands again.</i>

68
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:30,001
<i>To Garnett. Back to Kobe!</i>

69
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:31,085
Oh!

70
00:03:32,795 --> 00:03:35,423
He just wants to get
to the offensive end and go one-on-one.

71
00:03:35,506 --> 00:03:37,026
I'm gonna make his ass work down here.

72
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:38,771
He make it out,
we gotta get back!

73
00:03:39,427 --> 00:03:40,261
He hauling ass.

74
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:42,805
I ain't tryin' to be down there
on a poster, dog.

75
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:45,308
I ain't jumpin' with him. No.

76
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:47,745
It was a rough couple of years for me,
coming to the league.

77
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:50,649
At the time, the league was much older.
It's not as young as it is today.

78
00:03:51,147 --> 00:03:53,691
So, nobody was really thinking much of me.

79
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:57,445
I was the kid that... shot a bunch
of air-balls, you know what I mean?

80
00:03:58,029 --> 00:04:01,449
And at that point, Michael provided
a lot of guidance for me.

81
00:04:01,991 --> 00:04:04,702
I had a question
about shooting his turnaround shot,

82
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:05,995
so I asked him about it.

83
00:04:06,537 --> 00:04:09,165
And he gave me a great, detailed answer,

84
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:13,127
but on top of that, he said, "If you ever
need anything, give me a call."

85
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:15,463
He's like my big brother.

86
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:23,263
I truly hate having discussions
about who would win one-on-one,

87
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:26,933
and fans saying, "Kobe,
you'd beat Michael one-on-one."

88
00:04:27,016 --> 00:04:28,351
And I feel like, "Yo!

89
00:04:28,851 --> 00:04:31,187
What you get from me
is from him."

90
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:36,109
I don't get five championships here
without him,

91
00:04:36,192 --> 00:04:39,737
'cause he guided me so much
and he gave me so much great advice.

92
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,501
<i>Kobe had challenged Michael.</i>

93
00:04:41,572 --> 00:04:45,702
<i>Michael comes out and he's saying,
"Not tonight, young fella. Uh-uh, Kobe.</i>

94
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:47,954
<i>I got some more tricks left in my bag."</i>

95
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:50,415
<i>He's not ready to leave yet, folks.</i>

96
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,918
Great job, guys.
Hey, Jordan, you're my boy.

97
00:04:54,002 --> 00:04:56,254
Thank you. You know it, you know it.

98
00:04:56,337 --> 00:04:58,506
- I'll see you down the road.
- Cool.

99
00:04:58,589 --> 00:05:00,049
- Congratulations.
- You're my boy.

100
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,719
See you in the Finals. Hopefully.

101
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:05,138
- Y'all gonna be there.
- I know we will.

102
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:06,639
I ain't that soft!

103
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:08,223
Big Daddy!

104
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:11,394
I'm only gonna allow him
to have his trophy

105
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:14,355
if he promises to come back
and do it again.

106
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:22,780
The All-Star of All-Stars,
the MVP, Michael Jordan.

107
00:05:23,406 --> 00:05:24,615
If there was ever any doubt

108
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:27,785
that he could've kept playing
at an MVP and championship level...

109
00:05:28,619 --> 00:05:30,705
there's the All-Star Game, he's the MVP.

110
00:05:31,789 --> 00:05:34,375
He's still the star among stars.

111
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:37,503
Even though there were
explanations offered,

112
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:41,049
people couldn't understand
why he was gonna step away.

113
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,967
The public wanted him to keep going.

114
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:47,513
<i>A spectacular move!</i>

115
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:49,182
<i>The game's over!</i>

116
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:51,601
<i>Chicago Stadium is going wild!</i>

117
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:56,064
<i>First of all,
there's no backstabbing going on here.</i>

118
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:57,023
<i>It's time for me to move on.</i>

119
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:59,506
<i>This will be Phil's last year
as coach of the Bulls.</i>

120
00:06:02,111 --> 00:06:04,673
- <i>Are the expectations too high?
- Where do we go from here?</i>

121
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:07,200
<i>The only question: how long can it last?</i>

122
00:06:25,009 --> 00:06:29,430
Knowing this is the last dance,
unless something actually changes,

123
00:06:30,181 --> 00:06:32,350
I went into Madison Square Garden,

124
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:34,894
"This is the last time
I'm gonna be playing here."

125
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:37,397
And that was my favorite place to play.

126
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:43,945
Went back and grabbed
an old pair of Jordan 1s.

127
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:47,115
It's the first shoe I wore in the Garden,

128
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:49,158
so this was gonna be the last shoe,

129
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:51,482
being that this was the last time
I'd play in the Garden.

130
00:06:53,663 --> 00:06:56,165
<i>- ♪ Can I kick it? ♪
- ♪ Yes, you can! ♪</i>

131
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:58,668
<i>- ♪ Can I kick it? ♪
- ♪ Yes, you can! ♪</i>

132
00:06:58,751 --> 00:07:01,254
<i>- ♪ Well, I'm gone ♪
- ♪ Go on, then ♪</i>

133
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:05,216
<i>♪ Can I kick it?
To my Tribe that flows in layers... ♪</i>

134
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:08,094
Sweet. You laced those.

135
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:12,309
Toni, you weren't around.
You was a baby when I broke these out.

136
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:13,641
What was the year?

137
00:07:13,724 --> 00:07:16,519
- '84. How old were you?
- That's when I started.

138
00:07:16,602 --> 00:07:17,812
You were 12 years old.

139
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:19,801
Toni was still in diapers.

140
00:07:20,231 --> 00:07:21,732
You look at these shoes,

141
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:24,068
you put these shoes on
then put on some of them...

142
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:27,864
Innovation has taken a long turn.

143
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:50,970
I first met Michael Jordan in 1984.
I went to North Carolina

144
00:07:51,053 --> 00:07:53,473
to interview Michael and his family
to represent him.

145
00:07:55,516 --> 00:07:56,934
His parents asked great questions.

146
00:07:57,018 --> 00:07:59,645
They were very intelligent,
extremely personable.

147
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:04,692
Our firm, ProServ, had a lot of
very high-profile tennis clients,

148
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:07,320
like Jimmy Connors,
Stan Smith, Arthur Ashe.

149
00:08:07,945 --> 00:08:10,281
Arthur Ashe had his own shoes
and tennis racket.

150
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:15,495
This is the racket I won Wimbledon with.
You could've bought it. Really.

151
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:19,499
The strategy was to try to take
a team sport player

152
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:23,127
and treat him more like a golfer
or a boxer or a tennis player.

153
00:08:23,711 --> 00:08:25,922
I said to David,
"What are you trying to do?

154
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:28,424
You trying to turn this guy
into a tennis player?

155
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:31,427
He's a basketball player,
he's not a tennis player."

156
00:08:32,053 --> 00:08:36,807
I said, "That's exactly what I'm trying
to do." And the very first deal was shoes.

157
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:39,477
We took him out to meet Converse,

158
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:42,230
which, at that time,
was the official shoe of the NBA.

159
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:43,633
<i>♪ The Converse Weapon ♪</i>

160
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:46,776
<i>♪ That's the shoe lets Magic do
What he was born to do ♪</i>

161
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:51,072
<i>They have Magic Johnson,
Dr. J, Bernard King, Larry Bird...</i>

162
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:52,949
<i>♪ Y'all already know what you did for me ♪</i>

163
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:55,493
<i>- ♪ What? ♪
- ♪ I walked away with the MVP ♪</i>

164
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:58,663
<i>The Converse Weapon.
The number-one weapon in the NBA.</i>

165
00:08:58,746 --> 00:09:02,542
Converse had big players,
and told me, "We cannot...

166
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,336
envision you being put ahead of them."

167
00:09:06,045 --> 00:09:07,296
Okay. Fine.

168
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:10,067
Did you have a shoe company
that you wanted to go with?

169
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,091
That was Adidas.

170
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:15,263
I like the Lakers
and I like Marques Johnson.

171
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:17,765
And I like Adidas. I like the Adidas shoe.

172
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:21,811
Adidas was really dysfunctional
by that time.

173
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:24,313
They had just told me,
"We'd love to have Jordan.

174
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,983
We just can't make a shoe work
at this point in time."

175
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:31,779
I wanted Michael to go with Nike
because they were the upstart.

176
00:09:31,862 --> 00:09:37,118
In the early '80s, Nike was,
for the most part, a track shoe company.

177
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:41,330
Michael didn't even wanna be at Nike.

178
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:45,710
I couldn't even get him to get on
the damn plane and go visit the campus,

179
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:47,628
so I called his parents.

180
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:49,672
My mother said,
"You're gonna go listen.

181
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:51,882
You may not like it,
but you're gonna go listen."

182
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:54,677
"Mom, I don't wanna hear it.
I know what I wanna do.

183
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,554
I am not going to Nike's, Mama."

184
00:09:56,637 --> 00:10:00,516
I says, "Michael,
you have to give 'em an opportunity."

185
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,643
She made me go on that plane
and go listen.

186
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:06,772
I go into that meeting,
not wanting to be there.

187
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,525
Nike made this big pitch.

188
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:12,737
My father said, "You gotta be a fool
for not taking this deal."

189
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:20,786
Back then, the best guys might've gotten
$100,000 or so,

190
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:23,372
and he got probably $250,000.

191
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:24,457
It was like...

192
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:27,001
"You will pay him what?

193
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:29,045
A young rookie...

194
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:31,589
that's done nothing?

195
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:34,008
You must be out of your mind."

196
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:38,929
When I negotiated the Nike deal,
I said to them,

197
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:41,474
"You're a small company,
and if you want Michael Jordan,

198
00:10:41,557 --> 00:10:43,559
he's gotta have his own shoe line."

199
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:46,854
Nike had just come out
with this new technology

200
00:10:46,937 --> 00:10:49,398
for their running shoes called Air Soles.

201
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:51,567
And obviously, Michael played in the air.

202
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:53,819
I said, "I got it.
We're gonna call it Air Jordan."

203
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:58,449
"Air Jordan"?
That got a pretty good ring to it.

204
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:04,705
Nike's expectation,
when we signed the deal,

205
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:06,666
was at the end of year four,

206
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:10,419
they hoped to sell $3 million
worth of Air Jordans.

207
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,089
In year one, we sold $126 million.

208
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:14,691
<i>♪ I get paid when my record is played ♪</i>

209
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:15,883
<i>♪ To put it short ♪</i>

210
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:18,719
<i>♪ I got it made ♪</i>

211
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,016
<i>As a commodity,</i>

212
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,936
<i>Michael Jordan is as hot
as a Cabbage Patch doll right now.</i>

213
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:29,063
<i>The endorsements are fast and furious.</i>

214
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:31,482
<i>The photo sessions seem endless.</i>

215
00:11:31,565 --> 00:11:32,805
<i>Like a politician,</i>

216
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:34,898
<i>Jordan moves gracefully
through a crowd of admirers,</i>

217
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:37,988
<i>sipping orange juice,
collecting business cards.</i>

218
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:41,534
<i>Deals have already been cut with
Wilson Sporting Goods, McDonald's...</i>

219
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:49,208
For a kid, it was almost like...
holding a lightsaber from <i>Star Wars.</i>

220
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,544
You needed that shoe to be like him.

221
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:53,963
It was more than a status symbol.

222
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:56,257
You knew this guy was the guy.

223
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:58,926
<i>♪ 'Cause I got it made ♪</i>

224
00:11:59,009 --> 00:12:00,928
They came in different styles.

225
00:12:01,011 --> 00:12:04,223
The other brands didn't change too much.
Jordans changed with the times.

226
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:07,768
Everybody was like,
"You gotta get a pair of Jordans."

227
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:11,313
And so, every year we would save up money.

228
