358
00:20:11,501 --> 00:20:13,545
<i>Four-point Chicago lead.</i>

359
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:17,090
<i>Drexler with the check. He thought
there might be a timeout remaining.</i>

360
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:29,061
<i>The Chicago Bulls have won
the NBA championship</i>

361
00:20:29,144 --> 00:20:31,230
<i>for the second straight season!</i>

362
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:41,949
One is great, two is almost impossible.
Congratulations, Chicago.

363
00:20:42,532 --> 00:20:44,993
This is the happiest moment
in many, many years!

364
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:48,997
It feels so good. Oh, boy!

365
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:52,709
The one thing I would say, and I'd say it
from Jerry Reinsdorf on down,

366
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:54,795
this is a great organization.

367
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:56,880
This organization is special.

368
00:20:56,964 --> 00:21:00,259
From Jerry... It starts with Jerry,
and it goes down all the way to Joe Lee,

369
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,761
our clubhouse guy
who's been here 25 years.

370
00:21:02,844 --> 00:21:05,514
It's an organization thing,
and that's what it's all about.

371
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:08,850
The team is great, but the organization
is one of the all-time great,

372
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:12,521
if not the greatest organization ever.
That's what I'm so much proud of.

373
00:21:14,356 --> 00:21:16,608
